-- MOVES-State Street appoints Wai Kwong Seck to its management committee
-- By Luke Koshi in Bengaluru
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 03:39AM EST
-- None



Dec 18 (Reuters) - State Street Corp <STT.N>, the world's second-largest standalone custody bank, appointed Wai Kwong Seck to its management committee, the company's senior-most strategy and policy making group.

He is currently head of the company's Global Services and Global Markets businesses in Asia Pacific region since 2011. The company has also promoted Gunjan Kedia to the management committee.